Exercise 05 — Return-to-libc (NX Bypass)
==========================================

The stack is no longer executable. Shellcode injection is dead.

Instead, you will reuse code already in memory:
chain the address of system() with the address of "/bin/sh"
to get a shell — without writing a single byte of shellcode.

  Compile (NX on by default, no canary, no PIE):
    gcc -fno-stack-protector -no-pie -o target target.c

  Find the three addresses you need (in gdb):
    p system                              → address of system()
    p exit                                → address of exit()
    find &system,+9999999,"/bin/sh"       → address of "/bin/sh" in libc

  On x86_64, arguments go in registers, not on the stack.
  You need a 'pop rdi ; ret' gadget to load "/bin/sh" into rdi:
    ROPgadget --binary target | grep "pop rdi"

  Payload layout:
    [padding] + [pop_rdi gadget] + [addr of "/bin/sh"] + [addr of system] + [addr of exit]

  Once you have a shell, run:
    echo [SUCCESS]

Then run `horizon done`.
